==English==

===Etymology===
Plural of Italian [[putto]], 'male child', 'baby boy'.
===Noun===

{{en-noun|-}}

# {{art}} A usually winged, usually nude baby boy painted or carved into things such as [[cherub]]s or [[cupid]]s, and in fact defining the modern notion of a cherub or cupid. 
